title: Chick Corea & Stanley Clarke Pt 1: The Story Behind Return to Forever’s "Light as a Feather"
description:
Interested in learning directly from Chick? Join the Chick Corea Academy today! Click here now: https://www.chickcoreaacademy.com/
 
The founding members of Return to Forever, keyboardist Chick Corea and bassist Stanley Clarke, recently hung out at Chick’s masterclass, video production studio – Mad Hatter Studios East. The occasion was to deliver a free online music workshop to musicians all over the world. In this session, the inside story behind the classic album Light as a Feather is told.  

Light as a Feather was the band’s second release with Flora Purim on vocals, Joe Farrell on sax/flute and Airto Moreira on drums. The album has become a total classic and includes Chick’s most popular composition, "Spain."

The storyline in this video reveals how Stanley’s first-ever composition ends up being the title track of this timeless Return to Forever record. And a huge bonus is seeing these long-time friends and musical partners deliver a beautiful duet version of Stanley’s tune.  

Watch them play "Light as a Feather" here- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u2jxCvNb6dY

Website - http://bit.ly/1zfUlDH
Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/chickcorea
fulltitle: Chick Corea & Stanley Clarke Pt 1: The Story Behind Return to Forever’s "Light as a Feather"
